1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,912
The rule for picking a model is: let each one play to its sweet spot.

2
00:00:04,862 --> 00:00:11,175
Don't use Opus to grade multiple-choice questions, and don't use Haiku to debate methodology.

3
00:00:11,175 --> 00:00:16,075
Make the decision based on task characteristics, not model pricing.

4
00:00:16,075 --> 00:00:21,550
Your total cost will actually be lower than if you always picked the most powerful option.

